<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
	Real-Player phantom deployment groups (read by PhantomManager on boot).

	Each <population> spawns clientless real-Player phantoms into a hunting zone. Phantoms are
	scattered within the group's circle (center + radius) or, if a polygon is drawn, inside that
	shape; each spawn point is Z-snapped to the ground via geodata so they do not stack or float.

	ON-DEMAND: phantoms are NOT created at boot. A group spawns when a real player comes within
	(radius + ~2000) of its center, and despawns ~30s after the last player leaves the area (its
	DB rows are deleted on despawn, so nothing leaks). Each visit rolls a fresh crowd.

	Attributes:
	  name      - label for logs (optional).
	  x, y, z   - group center / anchor (required).
	  radius    - circular scatter radius around the center (default 800). Ignored if a polygon
	              of 3+ <point> children is given.
	  count     - how many phantoms to deploy (default 0 = nothing).
	  minLevel  - lowest level rolled (default 1).
	  maxLevel  - highest level rolled (default = minLevel). Each phantom rolls a level in the range.
	  respawn   - true (default): when a phantom dies it is despawned and a fresh one is spawned
	              into the same group a short while later. false: dead phantoms are not replaced.
	  role      - (optional) makes this a SUPPORT BUDDY instead of a field hunter. One of:
	              BUDDY_ELDER (Elven Elder - mage buffs, heals, recharge),
	              BUDDY_PROPHET (Prophet - fighter buffs), or
	              BUDDY_WARCRYER (Warcryer - Orc buffs). A buddy spawns idle where placed (it does NOT hunt).
	              Whisper it to party up (you invite, it auto-accepts), then it keeps you buffed and topped up
	              to ~half health, follows you, warns when low on MP, and teleports to a named gatekeeper
	              destination on command ("going to ruins of agony"). Place buddies in town at level 40+ so
	              they have a real buff kit; count = how many copies to offer.
	  regularCount  - (optional, default 0) auto-generate this many stable "regular" identities for the group,
	              with NO manual authoring. Each is built from a fixed seed (population name + slot), so the
	              same slot is the same name/appearance/class on every restart. Easiest way to get recurring
	              faces. Combine with <regular> children to mix hand-picked characters and auto ones.
	  regularChance - (optional, default 25) % chance a spawn uses one of this group's regular identities
	              (authored or auto-generated) instead of a fresh random one. Only matters if regulars exist.

	Regulars - recurring, recognizable faces (regularCount and/or <regular> children):
	  By default every spawn is a brand-new random identity, so the "person" you chatted with yesterday is
	  gone. Regulars are fixed identities that keep the SAME name and appearance every time they spawn. The
	  LLM brain hashes the name into a persistent personality, so a regular also sounds the same each session -
	  a character you actually recognize. The rest of the crowd stays randomized. A regular is never spawned
	  twice at once. Two ways to define them (mixable):
	    - regularCount="N"  -> auto-generate N stable regulars (no authoring; recommended).
	    - <regular .../>     -> hand-pick a specific name/look/class (below).
	  (Identity only for now: the phantom is still ephemeral - not yet a persistent character or friend. Player-
	  crafted phantoms and persistence/friends come in a later phase.)
	  <regular> attributes:
	    name      - the fixed character name (required; must be a valid, unique character name).
	    female    - true/false (default false).
	    face      - 0-2 (default 0).      hairColor - 0-3 (default 0).      hairStyle - 0-2 (default 0).
	    classId   - (optional) pin the class too, e.g. 0 Human Fighter, 10 Human Mage, 18 Elven Fighter,
	                25 Elven Mystic, 31 Dark Fighter, 38 Dark Mystic, 44 Orc Fighter, 53 Dwarven Fighter.
	                Omit (or 0) to let the class roll each spawn (only name/appearance are pinned).
	                Ignored for buddy populations (they keep their support class).

	Optional area instead of a circle - draw a polygon with <point> children:
	  <population name="..." x="..." y="..." z="..." count="10" minLevel="20" maxLevel="30">
	    <point x="..." y="..." />
	    <point x="..." y="..." />
	    <point x="..." y="..." />
	  </population>

	NOTE: phantoms only hunt when EnableAutoPlay = True in config/Custom/AutoPlay.ini.
	With no populations defined here, nothing auto-deploys (admin //phantom spawn still works).

	Example (commented out - edit/uncomment or manage via the fpc-editor tool):

	<population name="Giran Field" x="83400" y="147600" z="-3400" radius="1500" count="10" minLevel="20" maxLevel="30" respawn="true" />

	Easiest: auto-generate 4 stable regulars (no authoring), appearing ~40% of spawns:
	<population name="Giran Field" x="83400" y="147600" z="-3400" radius="1500" count="10" minLevel="20" maxLevel="30" regularCount="4" regularChance="40" />

	Or mix auto-generated regulars with a couple of hand-picked characters:
	<population name="Giran Field" x="83400" y="147600" z="-3400" radius="1500" count="10" minLevel="20" maxLevel="30" regularCount="3" regularChance="40">
		<regular name="Halvard" face="1" hairColor="0" hairStyle="2" classId="18" />
		<regular name="Sable" female="true" face="0" hairColor="2" hairStyle="1" classId="38" />
	</population>

	Support buddies idling in Giran (whisper one to party up - it then buffs/heals/follows you):
	<population name="Giran Elder" x="83400" y="147600" z="-3400" radius="120" count="1" minLevel="70" maxLevel="70" role="BUDDY_ELDER" />
	<population name="Giran Prophet" x="83430" y="147640" z="-3400" radius="120" count="1" minLevel="70" maxLevel="70" role="BUDDY_PROPHET" />
	<population name="Giran Warcryer" x="83370" y="147560" z="-3400" radius="120" count="1" minLevel="70" maxLevel="70" role="BUDDY_WARCRYER" />
-->
<list>
</list>
